00:51:09,840 --> 00:51:14,560
it, and now it's like this whole thing. So you've 
been in the middle of all that for a long time.  

539
00:51:14,560 --> 00:51:19,520
I guess just any thoughts on the importance of 
that and how you think about that as a founder?

540
00:51:19,520 --> 00:51:26,400
So founder mode means a lot of things to a lot 
of people. So it's a bit of a Rorschach test,  

541
00:51:28,280 --> 00:51:34,080
but I think parts of it that really resonate 
with me are, there's this evolution you go on  

542
00:51:34,080 --> 00:51:44,480
as a founder where you don't know what you're 
doing and everything is new and unfamiliar. And  

543
00:51:44,480 --> 00:51:47,640
then you're also very involved in all the details 
because there's no one else to be involved in the  

544
00:51:47,640 --> 00:51:54,000
details. It's not like someone else is coding 
for you if you're just in your room at home.  

545
00:51:55,840 --> 00:52:04,000
But then over time, you have to, there's this, Ben 
Horowitz calls it the Product-CEO Paradox, where  

546
00:52:04,720 --> 00:52:12,200
the first way that companies die is from founders 
not letting go. And so you need to learn to scale  

547
00:52:12,200 --> 00:52:18,160
yourself and hand off your responsibilities 
and operate at a higher level of abstraction.  

548
00:52:18,800 --> 00:52:22,960
But then the second way that companies kill 
themselves is the founders get too far away. 

549
00:52:22,960 --> 00:52:29,120
And I felt like I had done that. That's a big part 
of the problem that led to a lot of this chaos at  

550
00:52:29,120 --> 00:52:33,880
the end of chapter two, where I was like, oh, man, 
I'm on this treadmill. I'm doing stuff, but I'm  

551
00:52:33,880 --> 00:52:41,120
clearly not setting the right direction. Or people 
are confused or it's not working, and I was too  

552
00:52:41,120 --> 00:52:45,280
distant from the product. And then there's all 
kinds of issues you can get into as you hire an  

553
00:52:45,280 --> 00:52:52,080
executive team and get that to function well. And 
so I think there's a debate to what extent founder  

554
00:52:52,080 --> 00:52:58,760
